      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is a legal philosophy that argues the Constitution should be interpreted based on the original understanding at the time it was adopted. Proponents believe this approach maintains the rule of law and prevents judges from imposing their personal biases. They argue that this method respects the intentions of the Founding Fathers and preserves the stability and predictability of the legal system. Originalists often cite the importance of democratic principles, arguing that elected officials should make laws, not unelected judges.",
